                        "steps":  [
                                      "Take the steak out of the refrigerator and let it sit while you start the fries, even 10 to 15 minutes helps. Pat the steak very dry with paper towels so it sears instead of steaming.",
                                      "Preheat the air fryer to 400°F if your model recommends preheating. Add the frozen fries in as even a layer as possible and cook for 12 to 18 minutes total, shaking the basket halfway through and cooking in batches if crowded.",
                                      "While the fries cook, season the steak with kosher salt and black pepper, or use a light coating of premade steak rub. Use less salt if the rub already contains salt.",
                                      "Heat a cast-iron or heavy stainless skillet over medium-high to high heat until very hot. Add 1 tablespoon neutral oil, then lay in the steak without crowding the pan.",
                                      "Sear the steak until a deep brown crust forms. For strip, sirloin, or ribeye, cook about 3 to 5 minutes per side; for skirt steak or hanger steak, start checking closer to 2 to 4 minutes per side because thinner cuts cook faster.",
                                      "Move the steak to a cutting board and rest for 5 to 10 minutes. For medium-rare, pull around 125°F; for medium, pull around 135°F.",
                                      "Lower the pan to medium heat. If the pan has burned bits, wipe out only the blackened spots, but keep the browned steak drippings if they look golden-brown.",
                                      "Add 1 tablespoon butter and the garlic to the pan. Stir for about 30 seconds, then add beef broth and Worcestershire sauce if using, scraping up the browned bits from the bottom of the skillet.",
                                      "Simmer the pan sauce for 2 to 4 minutes, until slightly reduced and glossy. Turn off the heat and swirl in the remaining butter until the sauce looks smooth.",
                                      "Finish the fries while the steak rests, returning all fries to the air fryer for 2 to 3 minutes to re-crisp if needed. Slice the steak against the grain, especially for skirt or hanger steak, and serve with hot fries, pan sauce on the side or spooned lightly over the steak, and ketchup for fries if desired."
